SIMPLE: straggler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Straggler
<hw>Strag"gler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
straggles, or departs from the direct or proper course, or from the
company to which he belongs; one who falls behind the rest; one who
rambles without any settled direction.</def><-- they shot all the
stragglers -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A roving vagabond.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Something that shoots, or spreads out, beyond the
rest, or too far; an exuberant growth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let thy hand supply the pruning knife,⟦br⟧
And crop luxuriant <qex>stragglers</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Something that stands alone or by itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straggling</ent>⟦br⟧
